results.reasoning: Genetic condition characterized by continued fetal hemoglobin production into adulthood. Estimated ~0.5 per 100k based on hemoglobin variant studies and population genetics literature. Geographic variation significant with highest prevalence in African and Mediterranean populations.
results.source: Thein SL et al. (2000). Hereditary persistence of fetal hemoglobin. Hemoglobin. 24(2):123-146

results.reasoning: Most common skeletal dysplasia, caused by FGFR3 mutations. Global incidence ~2.5 per 100k births from multiple birth defect registries. Well-documented condition with consistent estimates across populations.
results.source: Horton WA et al. (2007). Standard nomenclature for achondroplasia. Am J Med Genet. 143A(1):1-7
